    "id": "CMP-BIN-001",
    "subject": "computer",
    "topic": "binary_logic_gates",
    "subtopic": "decimal_to_binary",
    "question": "What is the binary representation of the decimal number 13?",
    "options": {
      "A": "1011",
      "B": "1001",
      "C": "1101",
      "D": "1110"
    },
    "answer": "C",
    "explanation": "To convert 13 to binary: 13/2 = 6 rem 1. 6/2 = 3 rem 0. 3/2 = 1 rem 1. 1/2 = 0 rem 1. Reading remainders backwards gives 1101.",
    "difficulty": "easy",
